College Algebra is a course that covers the topics one would see in a typical Algebra 1 and 2 class. Whether you are a college freshman or an adult learner, College Algebra is often a required or introductory course to higher-level math courses. Many college students also have to complete college algebra simply to fulfill the math course requirements of their major. Work toward mastering the subject with Varsity Tutors’ free College Algebra app for Android-powered smartphones and tablets today.

For some students, the jump from mathematics that does not include variables to a math course that is seemingly filled with letters (variables) can be daunting. Make use of the free resourced offered on the Varsity Tutors College Algebra app for Android devices to increase your chances of success in the class. For example, you can take a diagnostic test offered in the app to identify what you already know, and what you may need additional work on when it relates to College Algebra.

A student can use utilize the 56 College Algebra practice tests offered on the app to decrease test-day jitters. For ongoing study, use the question of the day feature within the app to challenge yourself daily with a College Algebra question.

You can maximize your chances of success in College Algebra through a combination of careful study, daily practice, and utilizing appropriate study tools. The free Varsity Tutors College Algebra app for Android-powered smartphones and tablets is here to provide you with some tools for your personalized use. Whether it is working through an entire practice test or a single question of the day, you can take on College Algebra with a number of resources within easy reach.
